The press briefing held on September 1, 2017, addressed various topics including Hurricane Harvey relief efforts, the National Day of Prayer, the President's upcoming visits to Texas, foreign leader calls, upcoming White House visits, the DACA decision, the border wall, tax reform, infrastructure, and the investigation into the dismissal of FBI Director James Comey. The briefing also mentioned the President's commitment to job creation and the importance of tax reform. The details regarding the DACA decision and the infrastructure bill were not finalized at the time of the briefing.